Dr Macha, who suffered visual impairment at the age of five months due to measles, died on March 31 while undergoing treatment at the New Cross Hospital in Wolvehampton, United Kingdom (UK).Government officials, MPs and guests gathered at the August House grounds for a requiem mass, led by Assistant Bishop Samuel Muhina of KKKT Dodoma, to celebrate her life and pay last respects to Dr Macha who will be laid to rest today at Kirua Vunjo, Moshi Rural, Kilimanjaro Region.Dignitaries from both sides of the political divide paid a glowing tribute to Dr Mach recounting her great contribution within and outside the Parliament in defending the rights of people living with disabilities and the public in general.